President Obama has declared a major disaster in the state of Minnesota due to severe storms, straight-line winds, flooding, landslides, and mudslides that occurred between June 11 and July 11, 2014. Federal aid will be provided to supplement state and local recovery efforts. The funding will be available for emergency work, repair or replacement of damaged facilities, and hazard mitigation measures. The affected counties are Chippewa, Freeborn, Jackson, Murray, Nobles, Pipestone, Renville, and Rock. Warren J. Riley has been appointed as the Federal Coordinating Officer for federal recovery operations. Damage surveys are still ongoing, and more counties and forms of assistance may be designated in the future. For more information, contact the FEMA News Desk.